    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.invoices.lineItems.create(invoice_id: string, name: string, unit_amount: number, description?: string, direction?: string, metadata?: object, quantity?: number, unit_amount_decimal?: string): { id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; description: string; direction: string; invoice_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; name: string; object: string; quantity: number; unit_amount: number; unit_amount_decimal: string; updated_at: string; }`\n\n**post** `/api/invoices/{invoice_id}/invoice_line_items`\n\ncreate invoice_line_item\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `invoice_id: string`\n\n- `name: string`\n  The name of the line item, typically a product or SKU name.\n\n- `unit_amount: number`\n  The cost per unit of the product or service that this line item is for,           specified in the invoice currency's smallest unit.\n\n- `description?: string`\n  An optional free-form description of the line item.\n\n- `direction?: string`\n  Either `debit` or `credit`. `debit` indicates that a client owes the business money           and increases the invoice's `total_amount` due. `credit` has the opposite intention and effect.\n\n- `metadata?: object`\n  Additional data represented as key-value pairs. Both the key and value must be strings.\n\n- `quantity?: number`\n  The number of units of a product or service that this line item is for.           Must be a whole number. Defaults to 1 if not provided.\n\n- `unit_amount_decimal?: string`\n  The cost per unit of the product or service that this line item is for,           specified in the invoice currency's smallest unit. Accepts decimal strings with up to 12 decimals\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; description: string; direction: string; invoice_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; name: string; object: string; quantity: number; unit_amount: number; unit_amount_decimal: string; updated_at: string; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `amount: number`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `description: string`\n  - `direction: string`\n  - `invoice_id: string`\n  - `live_mode: boolean`\n  - `metadata: object`\n  - `name: string`\n  - `object: string`\n  - `quantity: number`\n  - `unit_amount: number`\n  - `unit_amount_decimal: string`\n  - `updated_at: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport ModernTreasury from 'modern-treasury';\n\nconst client = new ModernTreasury();\n\nconst invoiceLineItem = await client.invoices.lineItems.create('invoice_id', { name: 'name', unit_amount: 0 });\n\nconsole.log(invoiceLineItem);\n```",
