    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.ledgerEntries.list(id?: string[], after_cursor?: string, amount?: { eq?: number; gt?: number; gte?: number; lt?: number; lte?: number; }, as_of_lock_version?: number, direction?: 'credit' | 'debit', effective_at?: object, effective_date?: object, ledger_account_category_id?: string, ledger_account_id?: string, ledger_account_lock_version?: object, ledger_account_payout_id?: string, ledger_account_settlement_id?: string, ledger_account_statement_id?: string, ledger_transaction_id?: string, metadata?: object, order_by?: { created_at?: 'asc' | 'desc'; effective_at?: 'asc' | 'desc'; }, per_page?: number, show_balances?: boolean, show_deleted?: boolean, status?: 'pending' | 'posted' | 'archived', updated_at?: object): { id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; direction: transaction_direction; discarded_at: string; effective_at: string; ledger_account_currency: string; ledger_account_currency_exponent: number; ledger_account_id: string; ledger_account_lock_version: number; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; resulting_ledger_account_balances: ledger_balances; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; updated_at: string; }`\n\n**get** `/api/ledger_entries`\n\nGet a list of all ledger entries.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `id?: string[]`\n  If you have specific IDs to retrieve in bulk, you can pass them as query parameters delimited with `id[]=`, for example `?id[]=123&id[]=abc`.\n\n- `after_cursor?: string`\n\n- `amount?: { eq?: number; gt?: number; gte?: number; lt?: number; lte?: number; }`\n  Use `gt` (>), `gte` (>=), `lt` (<), `lte` (<=), or `eq` (=) to filter by amount.\n  - `eq?: number`\n  - `gt?: number`\n  - `gte?: number`\n  - `lt?: number`\n  - `lte?: number`\n\n- `as_of_lock_version?: number`\n  Shows all ledger entries that were present on a ledger account at a particular `lock_version`. You must also specify `ledger_account_id`.\n\n- `direction?: 'credit' | 'debit'`\n  If true, response will include ledger entries that were deleted. When you update a ledger transaction to specify a new set of entries, the previous entries are deleted.\n\n- `effective_at?: object`\n  Use `gt` (>), `gte` (>=), `lt` (<), `lte` (<=), or `eq` (=) to filter by the transaction's effective time. Format ISO8601\n\n- `effective_date?: object`\n  Use `gt` (>), `gte` (>=), `lt` (<), `lte` (<=), or `eq` (=) to filter by the transaction's effective date. Format YYYY-MM-DD\n\n- `ledger_account_category_id?: string`\n  Get all ledger entries that match the direction specified. One of `credit`, `debit`.\n\n- `ledger_account_id?: string`\n\n- `ledger_account_lock_version?: object`\n  Use `gt` (>), `gte` (>=), `lt` (<), `lte` (<=), or `eq` (=) to filter by the lock_version of a ledger account. For example, for all entries created at or before before lock_version 1000 of a ledger account, use `ledger_account_lock_version%5Blte%5D=1000`.\n\n- `ledger_account_payout_id?: string`\n\n- `ledger_account_settlement_id?: string`\n\n- `ledger_account_statement_id?: string`\n  Get all ledger entries that are included in the ledger account statement.\n\n- `ledger_transaction_id?: string`\n\n- `metadata?: object`\n  For example, if you want to query for records with metadata key `Type` and value `Loan`, the query would be `metadata%5BType%5D=Loan`. This encodes the query parameters.\n\n- `order_by?: { created_at?: 'asc' | 'desc'; effective_at?: 'asc' | 'desc'; }`\n  Order by `created_at` or `effective_at` in `asc` or `desc` order. For example, to order by `effective_at asc`, use `order_by%5Beffective_at%5D=asc`. Ordering by only one field at a time is supported.\n  - `created_at?: 'asc' | 'desc'`\n  - `effective_at?: 'asc' | 'desc'`\n\n- `per_page?: number`\n\n- `show_balances?: boolean`\n  If true, response will include the balances attached to the ledger entry. If there is no balance available, null will be returned instead.\n\n- `show_deleted?: boolean`\n  If true, response will include ledger entries that were deleted. When you update a ledger transaction to specify a new set of entries, the previous entries are deleted.\n\n- `status?: 'pending' | 'posted' | 'archived'`\n  Get all ledger entries that match the status specified. One of `pending`, `posted`, or `archived`. For multiple statuses, use `status[]=pending&status[]=posted`.\n\n- `updated_at?: object`\n  Use `gt` (>), `gte` (>=), `lt` (<), `lte` (<=), or `eq` (=) to filter by the posted at timestamp. For example, for all times after Jan 1 2000 12:00 UTC, use updated_at%5Bgt%5D=2000-01-01T12:00:00Z.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; direction: 'credit' | 'debit'; discarded_at: string; effective_at: string; ledger_account_currency: string; ledger_account_currency_exponent: number; ledger_account_id: string; ledger_account_lock_version: number; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; resulting_ledger_account_balances: { available_balance: ledger_balance; pending_balance: ledger_balance; posted_balance: ledger_balance; }; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; updated_at: string; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `amount: number`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `direction: 'credit' | 'debit'`\n  - `discarded_at: string`\n  - `effective_at: string`\n  - `ledger_account_currency: string`\n  - `ledger_account_currency_exponent: number`\n  - `ledger_account_id: string`\n  - `ledger_account_lock_version: number`\n  - `ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `live_mode: boolean`\n  - `metadata: object`\n  - `object: string`\n  - `resulting_ledger_account_balances: { available_balance: { amount: number; credits: number; currency: string; currency_exponent: number; debits: number; }; pending_balance: { amount: number; credits: number; currency: string; currency_exponent: number; debits: number; }; posted_balance: { amount: number; credits: number; currency: string; currency_exponent: number; debits: number; }; }`\n  - `status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'`\n  - `updated_at: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport ModernTreasury from 'modern-treasury';\n\nconst client = new ModernTreasury();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const ledgerEntry of client.ledgerEntries.list()) {\n  console.log(ledgerEntry);\n}\n```",
