    markdown:
      "## list\n\n`client.ledgerTransactions.versions.list(after_cursor?: string, created_at?: object, ledger_account_statement_id?: string, ledger_transaction_id?: string, per_page?: number, version?: object): { id: string; archived_reason: string; created_at: string; description: string; effective_at: string; effective_date: string; external_id: string; ledger_entries: object[]; ledger_id: string; ledger_transaction_id: string; ledgerable_id: string; ledgerable_type: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; partially_posts_ledger_transaction_id: string; posted_at: string; reversed_by_ledger_transaction_id: string; reverses_ledger_transaction_id: string; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; version: number; }`\n\n**get** `/api/ledger_transaction_versions`\n\nGet a list of ledger transaction versions.\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `after_cursor?: string`\n\n- `created_at?: object`\n  Use `gt` (>), `gte` (>=), `lt` (<), `lte` (<=), or `eq` (=) to filter by the created_at timestamp. For example, for all dates after Jan 1 2000 12:00 UTC, use created_at%5Bgt%5D=2000-01-01T12:00:00Z.\n\n- `ledger_account_statement_id?: string`\n  Get all ledger transaction versions that are included in the ledger account statement.\n\n- `ledger_transaction_id?: string`\n  Get all the ledger transaction versions corresponding to the ID of a ledger transaction.\n\n- `per_page?: number`\n\n- `version?: object`\n  Use `gt` (>), `gte` (>=), `lt` (<), `lte` (<=), or `eq` (=) to filter by the version. For example, for all versions after 2, use version%5Bgt%5D=2.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id: string; archived_reason: string; created_at: string; description: string; effective_at: string; effective_date: string; external_id: string; ledger_entries: { id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; direction: 'credit' | 'debit'; effective_at: string; ledger_account_currency: string; ledger_account_currency_exponent: number; ledger_account_id: string; ledger_account_lock_version: number; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; resulting_ledger_account_balances: object; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; }[]; ledger_id: string; ledger_transaction_id: string; ledgerable_id: string; ledgerable_type: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; partially_posts_ledger_transaction_id: string; posted_at: string; reversed_by_ledger_transaction_id: string; reverses_ledger_transaction_id: string; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; version: number; }`\n\n  - `id: string`\n  - `archived_reason: string`\n  - `created_at: string`\n  - `description: string`\n  - `effective_at: string`\n  - `effective_date: string`\n  - `external_id: string`\n  - `ledger_entries: { id: string; amount: number; created_at: string; direction: 'credit' | 'debit'; effective_at: string; ledger_account_currency: string; ledger_account_currency_exponent: number; ledger_account_id: string; ledger_account_lock_version: number; ledger_transaction_id: string; live_mode: boolean; metadata: object; object: string; resulting_ledger_account_balances: { available_balance: object; pending_balance: object; posted_balance: object; }; status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'; }[]`\n  - `ledger_id: string`\n  - `ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `ledgerable_id: string`\n  - `ledgerable_type: 'expected_payment' | 'incoming_payment_detail' | 'payment_order' | 'return' | 'reversal'`\n  - `live_mode: boolean`\n  - `metadata: object`\n  - `object: string`\n  - `partially_posts_ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `posted_at: string`\n  - `reversed_by_ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `reverses_ledger_transaction_id: string`\n  - `status: 'archived' | 'pending' | 'posted'`\n  - `version: number`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport ModernTreasury from 'modern-treasury';\n\nconst client = new ModernTreasury();\n\n// Automatically fetches more pages as needed.\nfor await (const ledgerTransactionVersion of client.ledgerTransactions.versions.list()) {\n  console.log(ledgerTransactionVersion);\n}\n```",
