    response:
      "{ id?: string; amount?: number; client_token?: string; counterparty_id?: string; created_at?: string; currency?: string; direction?: 'credit' | 'debit'; due_date?: string; effective_date_selection_enabled?: boolean; existing_external_accounts_filter?: 'verified'; external_account_collection?: 'disabled' | 'enabled'; live_mode?: boolean; object?: string; originating_account_id?: string; payment_order_id?: string; receiving_account_id?: string; selected_effective_date?: string; status?: 'cancelled' | 'completed' | 'expired' | 'pending'; updated_at?: string; }",
    markdown:
      "## create\n\n`client.paymentFlows.create(amount: number, counterparty_id: string, currency: string, direction: 'credit' | 'debit', originating_account_id: string, due_date?: string): { id?: string; amount?: number; client_token?: string; counterparty_id?: string; created_at?: string; currency?: string; direction?: 'credit' | 'debit'; due_date?: string; effective_date_selection_enabled?: boolean; existing_external_accounts_filter?: 'verified'; external_account_collection?: 'disabled' | 'enabled'; live_mode?: boolean; object?: string; originating_account_id?: string; payment_order_id?: string; receiving_account_id?: string; selected_effective_date?: string; status?: 'cancelled' | 'completed' | 'expired' | 'pending'; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n**post** `/api/payment_flows`\n\ncreate payment_flow\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `amount: number`\n  Required. Value in specified currency's smallest unit. e.g. $10 would be represented as 1000. Can be any integer up to 36 digits.\n\n- `counterparty_id: string`\n  Required. The ID of a counterparty associated with the payment. As part of the payment workflow an external account will be associated with this model.\n\n- `currency: string`\n  Required. The currency of the payment.\n\n- `direction: 'credit' | 'debit'`\n  Required. Describes the direction money is flowing in the transaction. Can only be `debit`. A `debit` pulls money from someone else's account to your own.\n\n- `originating_account_id: string`\n  Required. The ID of one of your organization's internal accounts.\n\n- `due_date?: string`\n  Optional. Can only be passed in when `effective_date_selection_enabled` is `true`. When set, the due date is shown to your end-user in the pre-built UI as they are selecting a payment `effective_date`.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ id?: string; amount?: number; client_token?: string; counterparty_id?: string; created_at?: string; currency?: string; direction?: 'credit' | 'debit'; due_date?: string; effective_date_selection_enabled?: boolean; existing_external_accounts_filter?: 'verified'; external_account_collection?: 'disabled' | 'enabled'; live_mode?: boolean; object?: string; originating_account_id?: string; payment_order_id?: string; receiving_account_id?: string; selected_effective_date?: string; status?: 'cancelled' | 'completed' | 'expired' | 'pending'; updated_at?: string; }`\n\n  - `id?: string`\n  - `amount?: number`\n  - `client_token?: string`\n  - `counterparty_id?: string`\n  - `created_at?: string`\n  - `currency?: string`\n  - `direction?: 'credit' | 'debit'`\n  - `due_date?: string`\n  - `effective_date_selection_enabled?: boolean`\n  - `existing_external_accounts_filter?: 'verified'`\n  - `external_account_collection?: 'disabled' | 'enabled'`\n  - `live_mode?: boolean`\n  - `object?: string`\n  - `originating_account_id?: string`\n  - `payment_order_id?: string`\n  - `receiving_account_id?: string`\n  - `selected_effective_date?: string`\n  - `status?: 'cancelled' | 'completed' | 'expired' | 'pending'`\n  - `updated_at?: string`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport ModernTreasury from 'modern-treasury';\n\nconst client = new ModernTreasury();\n\nconst paymentFlow = await client.paymentFlows.create({\n  amount: 0,\n  counterparty_id: '182bd5e5-6e1a-4fe4-a799-aa6d9a6ab26e',\n  currency: 'currency',\n  direction: 'credit',\n  originating_account_id: '182bd5e5-6e1a-4fe4-a799-aa6d9a6ab26e',\n});\n\nconsole.log(paymentFlow);\n```",
