    markdown:
      "## validate_routing_number\n\n`client.validations.validateRoutingNumber(routing_number: string, routing_number_type: string): { bank_address?: address_request; bank_name?: string; routing_number?: string; routing_number_type?: string; sanctions?: object; supported_payment_types?: string[]; }`\n\n**get** `/api/validations/routing_numbers`\n\nValidates the routing number information supplied without creating a routing detail\n\n### Parameters\n\n- `routing_number: string`\n  The routing number that is being validated.\n\n- `routing_number_type: string`\n  The type of routing number. See https://docs.moderntreasury.com/platform/reference/routing-detail-object for more details. In sandbox mode we currently only support `aba` and `swift` with routing numbers '123456789' and 'GRINUST0XXX' respectively.\n\n### Returns\n\n- `{ bank_address?: { country?: string; line1?: string; line2?: string; locality?: string; postal_code?: string; region?: string; }; bank_name?: string; routing_number?: string; routing_number_type?: string; sanctions?: object; supported_payment_types?: string[]; }`\n\n  - `bank_address?: { country?: string; line1?: string; line2?: string; locality?: string; postal_code?: string; region?: string; }`\n  - `bank_name?: string`\n  - `routing_number?: string`\n  - `routing_number_type?: string`\n  - `sanctions?: object`\n  - `supported_payment_types?: string[]`\n\n### Example\n\n```typescript\nimport ModernTreasury from 'modern-treasury';\n\nconst client = new ModernTreasury();\n\nconst routingNumberLookupRequest = await client.validations.validateRoutingNumber({ routing_number: 'routing_number', routing_number_type: 'aba' });\n\nconsole.log(routingNumberLookupRequest);\n```",
